Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The peacock, _Pavo cristatus_, is a resident breeder across the Indian subcontinent. Virtually all birds are considered susceptible to infection with Newcastle disease virus (NDV; Fam. Paramyxoviridae).

Pictures of the 2 dead peacocks can be accessed at http://www.brecorder.com/images/2013/07/ranikhet.jpg. - Mod.PMB

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1iGJ.]
